at%20if%20I%20forget%20to%20have%20kids%3F%26quot%3B%20Then%2C%20at%2046%2C%20I%20met%20my%20second%20husband%2C%20Jamey%2C%20now%2050.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tried%20for%20a%20baby%20the%20minute%20we%20were%20together.%20But%20we%20didn't%20conceive.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-different-ways-adoption-natural-conception-4-2022%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20looked%20into%20adoption%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0but%20the%20cost%20was%20prohibitive.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Also%2C%20it%20might%20have%20taken%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELuckily%2C%20Jamey's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fauto-insurance%2Fwhat-is-an-insurance-premium%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompany%20health%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20covered%20about%2085%25%20of%20fertility%20treatments.%20So%20we%20decided%20to%20try%20IVF.%20The%20doctors%20said%20my%20eggs%20were%20too%20old%20to%20be%20viable%20at%2049%2C%20and%20we%20should%20choose%20a%20donor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20I%20had%20a%20full%20exam%20to%20check%20whether%20my%20body%20could%20carry%20a%20baby.%20I%20had%20surgery%20to%20remove%20some%20polyps%20from%20my%20uterus.%20Then%2C%20we%20picked%20a%20donor%20who%20had%20a%20similar%20profile%20to%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20eggs%20were%20fertilized%20by%20Jamey's%20sperm%2C%20and%20I%20was%20placed%20on%20the%20hormones%20to%20get%20ready%20for%20the%20transfer.%20It%20took%20two%20attempts%2C%20but%20we%20were%20lucky%20enough%20to%20get%20pregnant%20in%20July%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d215efa5-bb76-48a2-967c-53d7fe5d1f2b%5C%22%3EI%20took%20a%20year%20off%20touring%20after%20my%20son%20was%20born%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pregnancy%20was%20super%20easy.%20I%20did%20yoga%20throughout.%20We%20hoped%20for%20a%20natural%20birth%2C%20and%20my%20doctor%20said%20that%20would%20be%20fine.%20She%20said%20that%20I%20was%20healthier%20than%20many%2020-year-olds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20baby%20had%20other%20ideas.%20I%20was%20induced%20due%20to%20back%20labor%20but%20was%20told%20it%20could%20take%2036%20hours%20for%20me%20to%20be%20dilated%20enough%20to%20deliver.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-kids-born-c-section-powerful-way-to-give-birth-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWe%20opted%20for%20a%20C-section%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20go%20through%20all%20that%20and%20end%20up%20needing%20an%20emergency%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20son%2C%20Huck%2C%20was%20born%20healthy.%20I%20fell%20in%20love%20with%20him%20the%20moment%20he%20was%20placed%20in%20my%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20went%20through%20the%20usual%20thing%20of%20sleepless%20nights%20for%20four%20months%20when%20you%20can't%20see%20straight.%20But%20things%20got%20better.%20I%20played%20a%20festival%20when%20I%20brought%20him%20along%20with%20support%20from%20my%20mother-in-law.%20It%20was%20hard%20because%20I%20was%20nursing%20and%20pumping.%20I%20realized%20I%20would%20just%20be%20home%20with%20him%20and%20took%20a%20year%20off%20touring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mom%20embraces%20her%20son.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6745c47cfa0140cdd5657092%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpeace%2C%2056%2C%20with%20her%20son%2C%20Huck%2C%206.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jamey%20Wood%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20tired%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20think%20I%20got%20more%20tired%20than%20younger%20moms%20did.%20I%20remained%20active%20and%20meditated%20daily.%20My%20spirituality%20has%20made%20me%20more%20patient%20and%20calm.%20It's%20helped%20me%20deal%20with%20the%20reality%20that%20I'll%20be%20almost%2070%20when%20Huck%20graduates%20high%20school.%20I'll%20never%20see%20him%20when%20he%20reaches%20my%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2