ehalf.%20For%20users%2C%20this%20is%20the%20most%20convenient%2C%20hassle-free%20way%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F293978%2Fflour-mill-in-uttar-pradesh-pays-zero-electricity-bills-with-solar-panels%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20started%20with%20solar%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20a%20hypothetical%20breakdown%20of%20how%20it%20works%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20say%20we%20install%20a%20100%20kW%20plant%20at%20a%20commercial%20or%20industrial%20building.%20Once%20the%20plant%20is%20commissioned%2C%20a%20residential%20user%20living%20in%20an%20apartment%20reserves%202%20kW%20of%20the%20100%20kW%20capacity%20for%20Rs%201%20lakh.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEach%20kilowatt%20of%20solar%20typically%20generates%20around%204%20units%20per%20day%2C%20so%20the%20user%E2%80%99s%20reserved%20capacity%20would%20generate%20approximately%202%20kW%20*%204%20units%2Fday%20*%2030%20days%20%3D%20240%20kWh%20per%20month.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20commercial%20entity%20pays%20for%20this%20power%20at%20Rs%206%20per%20unit%2C%20resulting%20in%20Rs%201440%20of%20energy%20credits%20for%20the%20user%20every%20month%20(this%20continues%20recurrently%20for%20the%20next%2015%20years).%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIf%20the%20user%E2%80%99s%20power%20bill%20for%20that%20month%20was%20Rs%201%2C500%2C%20and%20they%20pay%20it%20through%20the%20SundayGrids%20platform%2C%20their%20energy%20credits%20are%20applied%2C%20reducing%20the%20bill%20to%20just%20Rs%2060.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F11%2FCopy-of-Infographic-website-4-1732195942.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Community%20Solar%20